According to the quantitative analyses based on mean values of normalized spot quantities for fibrinogen gamma spot on plasma gels (3 technical replicates), our results showed that there was a small decrease in P1 (1.05-fold) and it increased in P2 (1.2-fold) compared to control (Figures 2 and 3

). Similarly, prothrombin level (based on 1 replicate) decreased in S1 (8.5-fold) compared to control and increased again in S2 (4.1-fold) compared to S1 on serum gels (Figures 3 and 4
).
